Business Brief -- L.A. Gear Inc.:
   U.S. Accuses Sneaker Maker
   Of Cooperation in Boycott
The company said the charges involve events that occurred
more than two years ago, and that it previously has tried to
resolve the dispute with the U.S. agency. The company could
lose its export privileges and faces a potential $460,000
fine.
   L.A. Gear added that it "continues its policy of full
compliance with all laws, including all anti-boycott laws,
and intends to defend itself vigorously."